      <hedline>
        <hl1>Debating Global Warming</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Gordon F Kingsley letter asks what part greenhouse gases played in global warming during latest ice age</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>When people admire the undulating meadow behind my house, I tell them the beauty results from global warming. Thousands of years ago, large areas of North America were covered with a great ice sheet. When the earth warmed and the glaciers retreated, they left behind many things, including the moraine on which I built my house.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>When people admire the undulating meadow behind my house, I tell them the beauty results from global warming. Thousands of years ago, large areas of North America were covered with a great ice sheet. When the earth warmed and the glaciers retreated, they left behind many things, including the moraine on which I built my house.</p>
        <p>My question: How much carbon dioxide got trapped in the atmosphere as a result of fossil fuels burned at the end of the ice age 20,000 years ago and what part did greenhouse gases play in the warming of earth when the glaciers moved north?</p>
        <p>GORDON F. KINGSLEY  Wellesley, Mass.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
